## Styling conventions

Use Tailwind utility classes for everything — do not write custom CSS unless Tailwind cannot do it. The colour palette for outcome badges should be consistent everywhere: green-100 background with green-800 text for "agreed", red-100 with red-800 for "rejected", yellow-100 with yellow-800 for "callback", and gray-100 with gray-700 for "no_answer".

For the overall dashboard feel, use a white or very light gray background (bg-gray-50), clean card containers with bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100, and consistent padding of p-4 or p-6. The goal is something that looks like a real SaaS product, not a hackathon project.

