## npm packages I will need

Run these from inside the frontend/ folder.

For the map: npm install leaflet react-leaflet @types/leaflet
For data fetching with auto-refresh: npm install swr

Tailwind and TypeScript are already installed from create-next-app.

---

## Common mistakes to avoid

Never hardcode localhost:8000 as a string — put it in a NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL environment variable in a .env.local file inside the frontend/ folder so it can be changed without touching code.

When using Leaflet with Next.js App Router, the map component must be dynamically imported with { ssr: false } because Leaflet requires the browser window object and will crash during server-side rendering. Always wrap the map in a dynamic import.

When displaying timestamps from the database, always convert them to the user's local timezone using new Date(timestamp).toLocaleTimeString() — do not display raw UTC strings to users.

The call log must show the most recent call at the top, so always sort the calls array by called_at descending before rendering.
